Paleoenvironment. Ubiquitous in all shallow water deposits of the Karpatian and Badenian of the Central Paratethys but rare in offshore settings. It appears in seagrass assemblages (e.g. Gainfarn,
Zuschin et al . 2007
) and lagoonal environments (e.g. Korneuburg Basin,
Zuschin et al . 2014
). Stable isotope data suggest a preference for normal marine conditions without influx of brackish water (
Latal et al . 2006
).

